President Trump delivered remarks at the United Nations, expressing his support for the reform of the organization. He commended Secretary General Guterres for his efforts to make the United Nations more efficient and focused on results, rather than bureaucracy. Trump emphasized the need for accountability, clear goals, and metrics for success in peacekeeping missions. He called on member states to take bold stands and make necessary changes to ensure the United Nations fulfills its core mission. Trump pledged to be a partner in the reform process and expressed confidence that the United Nations will become a stronger force for peace and harmony in the world.